args:
The prince battles Barbary in the space between
worlds, but is unable to totally defeat her due
to the might of her furious counterattack.
Hoping to gain an advantage in the fight,
the prince decides to seek out Siren and
enlist the power of her song.
Gar, nobody makes a fool of a pirate!\nYe'll pay for this, ye will!
How is that fiend still standing?\nWe landed every blow clean!
Try usin' the fragment again, boss!
I'll send every last one of ye to\nthe darkest depths of the locker!
Nnngh... Her attack is unbelievable...\nWe're so busy dodging we can't even\nget a hit in!
Hold on! Lemme try a few arrows!
...Dammit! Those explosions are knocking\nmy arrows off course!
Gahar har! We're just gettin' started,\nso we are! Bring me the next one!
Those fiends are giving Barbary some kind\nof exploding weapon!
COME, YE SLIMY SCALLYWAGS!\nCOME FEEL THE FURY OF BARBARY!
Damn, this lady ain't messin' around!
Barbary has lost herself in her rage!
We can't keep this up or someone\nis going to get seriously hurt.
Everyone, fall back to Erasmus's cave!
I usually ain't much for runnin'\nbut watch these feet fly!
Yar, where be ye paddlin' off to?\nI gots another surprise for ye!
Argh, my eyes! That ain't fair, so it ain't!
Go, all of you! Take flight while you can!
Gar, ye be nothin' but a barrelful of\nlily-livered, yellow-bellied cowards!
Very well! Show me yer backs, cravens!\nWon't be long before I be rippin' apart\nevery last soul on this bedamned island!
Just in case anyone is curious,\nI am NOT a fan of this lady at ALL.
We had best take her at her word when\nshe claims the will to lay waste to the\nisland and all souls upon it.
But if I hadn't allowed her to take\nthe treasure from me...
The prince is correct—you did no wrong.
The responsibility for all falls to me;\nI was unable to protect the treasure.
You have now become ensnared in\ntroubles of my making, and for this,\nI am truly sorry.
You didn't do anything wrong either.
So let's all stop apologizing and instead\nfigure out what our next move should be.\nThere must be SOMETHING we can do!
Nothing is impossible if you\nbut possess the will!
If fighting spirit was all that was required\nfor victory, we would have already been\ndone with this long ago.
Then perhaps our spirit is simply lacking!

And perhaps it takes more than that!
I have a strong will, and yet recently I
found myself ensnared by a song more
powerful than any desire I have known.
No one—not even you—could hear that\nbeautiful singing and not be charmed!
Methinks an idea has just formed.
Guys, I think I know how we can defeat\nBarbary and save this island.
If we charm Barbary with Siren's song,\nit might be enough to slow her down.
We'll take advantage of that moment\nto use the otherworld fragment.
Trapping her in the space\nbetween worlds yet again!
Yeah, that's great and all, but it doesn't\nsolve the bigger problem of how to\nactually...you know? DEFEAT her?
It don't matter WHERE we fight if we don't\ndo somethin' about that weapon of hers.
I have an idea about that as well.\nSee, I think we need to—
To summon up our iron WILLS!\nIf she launches explosions,\nwe simply charge into them!
Would you please still your flapping gums\nand let him FINISH!?
Barbary only has so many bombs—\nshe uses her minions to resupply her.
So we have to isolate her in the space\nbetween worlds and cut her off from\nthose minions.
Though of course, she can still attack with\nthe bombs she has on hand, so we'll need\nto be cautious in any case.
This is a solid plan through and through.\nLet us go to Siren and beg her aid.
Give me your map, then, that I might\nmark Siren's dwelling upon it.
OR you could just guide us there yourself.\nI mean, if you wanna be heeeelpfull?
Siren despises me. If you hope to secure\nher cooperation, I will hinder your efforts.
How can she hate YOU, man?\nYou're totally rad!
As I stated before, I admonished Siren\nfor singing her song without taking\nits effects into account.
As the guardian dragon of all who voyage\non the high seas, I cannot turn a blind eye\nto the poor sailors she befuddles.
I do not hate her. I truly don't.\nHer voice is simply...too beautiful.
Looks like we'll have to meet\nwith Siren alone, then.

Yeah, but how do we even GET to her
when crazy eyepatch lady is gonna
open up on us the moment we step
foot outta this cave?
We should split into two groups.
While one of them keeps her busy,\nthe other can go to Siren.
So who draws the short straw\nof playin' target practice?
I know you said none of this was my fault,\nbut I still feel that I have failed somehow.

If she is going, then I will accompany her.
What kind of instructor would I be if I were
to let one of my charges run off into the
heart of danger all alone?
I will play the role of bait as well.\nSuch is my duty as a Paladyn.
And I will do the same.
No. Your duty lies with the prince.
In that case, I will trust you to take care\nof everyone in my stead.
I too will join the distraction team.\nPartly because I cannot appear before\nSiren...
But more so because I have a score\nto settle with Barbary. I do not wish\nto turn my back upon her.
I feel better already knowing I have\nall of you at my back.
I'll come back with Siren—I promise.\nJust hold out until then!
Then let's set this plan into motion!
